reviews.title: Prima 👍
reviews.text:
Delicious pancakes for a great price
Service cheerful, cozy and smooth
Besides pancakes extensive menu

reviews.title: Rude manager
reviews.text:
Staff was inexperienced but friendly.
Management was downright rude.

The food is very mediocre for what it costs. Especially the food for the kids. A childrens size pancake is about the size of a coaster (10cm in diameter) and costs nearly as much as an adult size pancake.

When we asked if the kitchen maybe made a mistake we were informed by the manager that all children's pancakes are that size.  She was overall very confrontational and rude. We were very uncomfortable with how we were addressed and surprised by the lack of professionalism.

reviews.title: The food and service were excellent! I can recommend it to everyone!
reviews.text:
Too bad they are only open until 8pm!
Otherwise I would definitely have a very nice evening there with friends!

reviews.title: Not recommended
reviews.text: It took a long time before we got food. The food was also poor for the price. Service is friendly and inexperienced. A nice playground for the children.

reviews.title: A bit overpriced restaurant at nice location
reviews.text: Restaurant where they serve various types of pancakes. The service is ok but the food is mediocre and rather expensive for what you get. The all you can eat option only had terrible sticky pancakes. For children it is ok as there are some play areas inside and outside.

articleContent.title: How to eat your way through Greenville, SC

seoInfo.metaDescription: For those who plan their meals before booking a plane ticket, listen up: There is a place where you can immerse yourself in the dining cultures of 34 countries across five continents without leaving a single city limit.
